    &lt;Title&gt;Wonderful care from The Colorectal Team and nurses on T5&lt;/Title&gt;
    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Denis O’Donnell&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;I was treated by the colorectal team on 12th June. The surgeon came to see me early in the morning before surgery and explained everything to me. My surgery was carried out in the afternoon and I was admitted to T5 to start my recovery. The surgeon contacted my wife at 9.45pm to let her know how the operation had gone which was beyond our expectations, especially knowing he had been working since the early morning. During my time on T5, I was constantly monitored and cared for. The nurses were brilliant, kind and compassionate and ensured that the ward was spotless and every patient’s needs were met. Over the next couple of weeks, the surgeon, his team and the Macmillan nurses looked after me and my family and we can’t thank them enough.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
